TITLE: Integrating Payload Hook with Request Transaction in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to ensure a database operation within a Payload `afterChange` hook is part of the main request's transaction. By passing the `req` object (which contains `req.transactionID` assigned by Payload) to the `req.payload.create` call, the creation of 'my-slug' will only be persisted if the entire original request, including the hook execution, completes successfully without errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/transactions.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
```ts
const afterChange: CollectionAfterChangeHook = async ({ req }) => {
  // because req.transactionID is assigned from Payload and passed through,
  // my-slug will only persist if the entire request is successful
  await req.payload.create({
    req,
    collection: 'my-slug',
    data: {
      some: 'data',
    },
  })
}
```
