TITLE: Extending Schema Before Initialization with Payload Postgres Adapter (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet leverages the beforeSchemaInit hook from the Payload CMS Postgres adapter to add custom tables to the database schema before initialization. It imports Drizzle schema utilities and extends the schema object by adding a new table ('added_table') with a serial primary key column. This allows users to preserve or introduce tables that are not managed through Payload's built-in configuration. Dependencies include @payloadcms/db-postgres and Drizzle's pg-core. The expected input is an initial schema object; the output is an augmented schema, with new tables merged in. Ensure that added tables do not conflict with Payload's managed collections.
SOURCE: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/database/postgres.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { postgresAdapter } from '@payloadcms/db-postgres'
import {
  integer,
  pgTable,
  serial,
} from '@payloadcms/db-postgres/drizzle/pg-core'

postgresAdapter({
  beforeSchemaInit: [
    ({ schema, adapter }) => {
      return {
        ...schema,
        tables: {
          ...schema.tables,
          addedTable: pgTable('added_table', {
            id: serial('id').notNull(),
          }),
        },
      }
    },
  ],
})
```

