TITLE: Creating a Login Server Action in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Next.js server action (`loginAction`) that wraps the Payload `login` function. It accepts user credentials (email, password), imports the Payload config, calls the `login` function, and handles potential errors. This server action pattern is necessary because the Payload config cannot be directly imported or used in client components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/local-api/server-functions.mdx#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
