TITLE: Implementing a Refresh Token Button React Client Component (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Provides a React client component (`RefreshTokenButton`) that renders a button. Clicking the button triggers the `refreshAction` server function to refresh the user's authentication token. Requires the `refreshAction` server function defined elsewhere (e.g., `../actions/refreshAction`). Note: The original example code calls `refreshFunction()`, which is likely a typo and should be `refreshAction()`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/local-api/server-functions.mdx#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
```tsx
'use client'

import { refreshAction } from '../actions/refreshAction' // Path to the server action

export default function RefreshTokenButton() {
  const handleRefresh = async () => {
    try {
      await refreshAction();
      // Handle successful refresh (e.g., update UI state if needed)
    } catch (error) {
      // Handle refresh error
      console.error(error);
    }
  };

  return <button onClick={handleRefresh}>Refresh</button>
}
```
```

