TITLE: Converting Lexical to HTML Asynchronously with Payload Local API (Server)
DESCRIPTION: Shows a server-side approach for asynchronous Lexical-to-HTML conversion using `convertLexicalToHTMLAsync` within a React Server Component (RSC) or similar server context. It utilizes `getPayloadPopulateFn` and the Payload Local API (`getPayload`) for efficient data population, avoiding multiple network requests. Requires access to the Payload configuration and instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/converting-html.mdx#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import type { SerializedEditorState } from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical/lexical'

import { getPayloadPopulateFn } from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical'
import { convertLexicalToHTMLAsync } from '@payloadcms/richtext-lexical/html-async'
import { getPayload } from 'payload'
import React from 'react'

import config from '../../config.js'

export const MyRSCComponent = async ({ // Note: This implies a Server Component context
  data,
}: {
  data: SerializedEditorState
}) => {
  const payload = await getPayload({
    config,
  })

  const html = await convertLexicalToHTMLAsync({
    data,
    populate: await getPayloadPopulateFn({
      currentDepth: 0,
      depth: 1,
      payload,
    }),
  })

  return html && <div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: html }} />
}
```

